President Obama announced his intent to nominate Amos J. Hochstein as the Assistant Secretary for Energy Resources at the Department of State. Hochstein is currently the Special Envoy and Coordinator for International Energy Affairs at the Department of State. He has previously held various positions in the government and private sector related to energy and international relations.

President Obama also announced his intent to nominate David McKean as the Ambassador to Luxembourg. McKean is currently serving as the Director of the Office of Policy Planning at the Department of State. He has extensive experience in foreign policy and has worked in various roles in government and non-profit organizations.

Additionally, President Obama announced his intent to appoint Raymond Dolan as a member of the President's National Security Telecommunications Advisory Committee. Dolan is currently the President and CEO of Sonus Networks and has held various executive roles in the telecommunications industry. He also has a background in the military, having served as a tactical jet pilot in the U.S. Marine Corps.